Templates.template:
new sap.ui.fl.variants.VariantManagement(
	"${sId}", // string
	{
		id: ${id}, // sap.ui.core.ID
		models: ${models}, // object
		bindingContexts: ${bindingContexts}, // object
		objectBindings: ${objectBindings}, // object
		metadataContexts: ${metadataContexts}, // object
		validationSuccess: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		validationError: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		parseError: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		formatError: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		modelContextChange: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		tooltip: ${tooltip}, // sap.ui.core.TooltipBase
		customData: [${customData}], // sap.ui.core.CustomData[]
		layoutData: ${layoutData}, // sap.ui.core.LayoutData
		dependents: [${dependents}], // sap.ui.core.Element[]
		dragDropConfig: [${dragDropConfig}], // sap.ui.core.dnd.DragDropBase[]
		blocked: ${bBlocked}, // boolean
		busy: ${bBusy}, // boolean
		busyIndicatorDelay: ${1000}, // int
		busyIndicatorSize: ${sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize.Medium}, // sap.ui.core.BusyIndicatorSize
		visible: ${bVisible}, // boolean
		fieldGroupIds: ${[]}, // string[]
		validateFieldGroup: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		showExecuteOnSelection: ${bShowExecuteOnSelection}, // boolean
		showSetAsDefault: ${bShowSetAsDefault}, // boolean
		manualVariantKey: ${bManualVariantKey}, // boolean
		inErrorState: ${bInErrorState}, // boolean
		editable: ${bEditable}, // boolean
		modelName: "${modelName}", // string
		updateVariantInURL: ${bUpdateVariantInURL}, // boolean
		resetOnContextChange: ${bResetOnContextChange}, // boolean
		for: [${for}], // (sap.ui.core.Control|string)[]
		save: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		manage: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		initialized: [function (oEvent) {}, this], // function|array
		select: [function (oEvent) {}, this] // function|array
	}
)
Templates.constructorDescription:
Constructor for a new VariantManagement. Accepts an object literal mSettings that defines initial property values, aggregated and associated objects as well as event handlers. See {@link sap.ui.base.ManagedObject#constructor} for a general description of the syntax of the settings object.

The supported settings are:

  • Properties
    • {@link #getShowExecuteOnSelection showExecuteOnSelection} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getShowSetAsDefault showSetAsDefault} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getManualVariantKey manualVariantKey} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getInErrorState inErrorState} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getEditable editable} : boolean (default: true)
    • {@link #getModelName modelName} : string
    • {@link #getUpdateVariantInURL updateVariantInURL} : boolean (default: false)
    • {@link #getResetOnContextChange resetOnContextChange} : boolean (default: true)
  • Associations
    • {@link #getFor for} : (sap.ui.core.ID | sap.ui.core.Control)[]
  • Events
    • {@link #event:save save} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:manage manage} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:initialized initialized} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
    • {@link #event:select select} : fnListenerFunction or [fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject] or [oData, fnListenerFunction, oListenerObject]
In addition, all settings applicable to the base type {@link sap.ui.core.Control#constructor sap.ui.core.Control} can be used as well.
Templates.name: sap.ui.fl.variants.VariantManagement
Templates.helpDescription:
Can be used to manage variants. You can use this control in most controls that are enabled for key user adaptation.
Note: On the user interface, variants are generally referred to as "views".

Templates.helpDescription: Fires event {@link #event:save save} to attached listeners.

Templates.name: sap.ui.fl.variants.VariantManagement.fireSelect
Templates.helpDescription: Fires event {@link #event:select select} to attached listeners.

setVariantProperties(
	"${sVariantManagementReference}", // sap.ui.fl.variants.VariantManagement
	{
		variantReference: ${variantReference}, // String
		changeType: ${changeType}, // String
		layer: ${layer}, // String
		appComponent: ${appComponent}, // String
		title: ${title}, // String
		visible: ${bVisible}, // boolean

	},
	"${bAddChange}" // boolean
)

Templates.helpDescription: Activates the passed variant applicable to the passed control/component.

Templates.name: sap.ui.fl.apply.api.ControlVariantApplyAPI.clearVariantParameterInURL
Templates.helpDescription: Clears URL technical parameter sap-ui-fl-control-variant-id for control variants. Use this method in case you normally want the variant parameter in the URL, but have a few special navigation patterns where you want to clear it. If you don't want that parameter in general, set the updateVariantInURL parameter on your variant management control to false. SAP Fiori elements use this method. If a variant management control is given as a parameter, only parameters specific to that control are cleared.
